message:
feat(codegen): Add withInlineBlock callback API to prevent double semicolons

Adds safe callback-based inline block API:
- with

InlineBlock(hint, context, callback) - automatic semicolon handling
- Can't forget to close blocks (compiler enforced)
- No more double semicolon bugs (;; )
- Context parameter allows easy variable capture

Example:
  try self.withInlineBlock("hint", args, struct {
      fn emit(c: *NativeCodegen, label: []const u8, a: []ast.Node) !void {
          try c.genExpr(a[0]);
          try c.emitBreak(label, "result");
      }
  }.emit);

Migrated 4 functions in os.zig as proof of concept:
- genListdir, genGetenv, genRename (all working)

Kept emitInlineBlockStart/End as DEPRECATED for backward compatibility.
Can migrate remaining 433 usages gradually or in bulk.

